nodes.text: The Kalikori Club was a restaurant, bar, and entertainment venue found in Black Spire Outpost on the planet Batuu. The somewhat hidden club included a table-service restaurant and live performers. It was owned by a female Twi'lek who was also one of the many performers at the club.

The Kalikori Club was a food and entertainment venue partially planned and announced during the development of Disney's Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge. Besides a table-service restaurant, it would have included entertainment in the form of alien singers and dancers. The concept included a Twi'lek proprieter and performer who may have also had ties to the underworld. That portion of her back story was given to Oga Garra instead. Various pieces of concept art were created and later released to media outlets, but the venue was ultimately canceled. Details and concept art were later published in The Art of Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge in 2021.
